SINGAPORE, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Singapore reported 5,605 new confirmed cases of COVID-19 on Thursday, bringing the total tally to 1,096,428. Of the new cases, 736 cases were detected through polymerase chain reaction (PCR) tests and 4,869 through antigen rapid test (ART) tests, according to statistics released by the Ministry of Health. Among the PCR cases, 718 were local transmissions and 18 were imported cases. Among the ART cases with mild symptoms and assessed to be of low risk, there were 4,741 local transmissions and 128 imported cases. A total of 646 cases are currently warded in hospitals, with 27 cases in intensive care units. Five more patients have died from complications due to COVID-19 infection, bringing the death toll to 1,268, the ministry said.  â– 